t class=m><span class=title>   Re: ToVN Rotation agreement/rules</span><hr size=1> Malaka,<br>
<br>
That is correct.<br>
<br>
It is an invalid argument to point out that BOTS killed Ikky and Eashan without killing Aary back in the day, because their actions then were not denying content to anyone.  They were the only guild in NTOV.  Once a rotation is established, we RESPECT the rotation.<br>
<br>
To use such an argument infers that BOTS is somehow to blame for the fact that you weren't in NTOV at that time.  You're saying, &quot;Well, BOTS didn't have to share the mobs when nobody else was there, so why do we have to share now that we have 3 guilds and over 150 people playing there?&quot;  Do you see the difference?<br>
<br>
Let's go back to preschool.  If you go out to the playground and nobody's playing on the slide, then you can slide ALL you want, but if someone else comes along, you take turns.  The new guy doesn't get to take posession of the slide because the other kid had it before he came along.<br>
<br>
The guilds who formed later or who are now becoming capable of killing end-game content are welcome to their place at the table on this server, but it does mean that the guys who were there first will have gotten a bigger share of things simply by favor of having been there longer with less competition.   By the time Tindi and Noble Blade go to Vex Thal, BOTS will have had a nice head start on the loot there, but we don't begrudge them that position.  They worked for it.  They, in fact, had to work harder than WE did, since BOTS got their Vex Thal crew together back when key drops were insanely rare.  <br>
<br>
The same applies to Velious content.  Back when BOTs, and to a lesser extent Tindi and NB were killing Velious content, we had to do it without the ability to breeze past certain steps and without some of the 'mudflation' ease that the newer guilds have now.  I'm not bragging or expressing arrogance.  I'm saying that it's not fair of guilds to look at 'the big three' and accuse us of oppressing smaller guilds.  We worked for our position, and we worked hard, in some cases harder than any guild in the present day will have to work to do the same thing.   If you come late to the buffet, you're going to find yourselves waiting in a longer line.  That doesn't make it not fair. <br>
<br>
On the Rathe, you have a UNIQUE opportunity.  We are the ONLY server in Everquest that has a self-managing system of SHARING the game content.  If you want to kill Yelinak on our server, you only have to race to that mob one time, and usually if you ask nicely the current rotation guild will even give you a shot without racing.  After that, you have your fair turn at the mob.  On any other server, you will race to that mob EVERY time you want to kill him, and guilds like BOTS, TIndi and NB on those servers work their asses off to keep guilds like yours from ever seeing a scrap.<br>
<br>
Borick Ascid<br>
High Priest of Brell<br>
Noble Blade<br>
The Rathe <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#222222><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ugrommofbots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gromm of BotS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Blood of the Spider</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 1:30:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ToVN Rotation agreement/rules</span><hr size=1> Well... Ikatair and Eashen were always done this way by convention by the guilds on the ToVN rotation.  With the recent Dozekar/Named issues, I figured now would be a good time to put it all down so we could avoid future mistakes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/umalakarude.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MalakaRude</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 275<br> <font color=#00FFFF>(9/16/02 2:23:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ftherathetravelagencyfrm50.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=123.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cs.vu.nl/~dhbergen/malaka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ToVN Rotation agreement/rules</span><hr size=1> well borick, there have been guilds when bots was already clearing whole ntov that was just killing iki and eashen 20+ times because they knew they couldnt kill aary. of course, at that time there wasnt any rotation set. <br>
